-- 
German Companies Have Record Cash Pile, Handelsblatt Reports

-- B y   H o l g e r   E l f e s
-- 
2011-05-24T06:44:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/german-companies-have-record-cash-pile-handelsblatt-reports.html
German companies had record cash of
121.5 billion euros ($171 billion) at the end of last year,
 Handelsblatt  reported today, citing a survey by
PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP.  The companies with the biggest cash piles were  Volkswagen
AG (VOW) ,  Siemens AG (SIE) ,  Daimler AG (DAI) ,  Bayerische Motoren Werke AG (BMW)  and  E.ON
AG (EOAN) , the newspaper said, adding that German companies will
probably accelerate investment and acquisition activities in the
coming months.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Holger Elfes in Dusseldorf at 
 helfes@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net  